      "content": "While it's natural to want to protect your children from pain, completely disconnecting from them would be deeply hurtful and likely traumatic for them. Remaining present and trying to be a better parent, despite your flaws, is actually the greatest act of selflessness and love you can show them. It may not be easy, but your vulnerability and willingness to learn and grow can ultimately help you build a stronger, more resilient relationship with your kids.",
      "source": "target",
